text: George Wilbur Peck was an authorWisconsin Encyclopedia By Jennifer L. Herman, 2008, P.213-214 and American Democratic Party politician who served as governor of Wisconsin from 1891 to 1895. During his time as governor, various measures were introduced such as an Act of 1893 that sought to safeguard corporations, persons or associations of workingmen in the use and enjoyment of their labels, trade-marks and forms of advertising.
